The article is a summary of an executive order signed by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. The order states that the policy of the administration is to address urgent challenges such as the COVID-19 pandemic, economic recovery, racial justice, and climate change. It revokes previous orders that hinder the government's ability to confront these issues and empowers agencies to use regulatory tools to achieve these goals. The Director of the Office of Management and Budget and agency heads are instructed to rescind any orders implementing the revoked executive orders. Any personnel positions, committees, or task forces established by the revoked orders will be abolished. The order does not affect the authority of executive departments or the functions of the Director of the Office of Management and Budget. It is to be implemented in accordance with applicable law and subject to appropriations.